Recommends: openresolv | resolvconf | systemd-resolved
Description: Native GTK4 WireGuard VPN client
 Wren is a modern GTK4 / libadwaita client for managing WireGuard VPN
 tunnels on Linux. It imports .conf files, connects and disconnects
 with one click via wg-quick (elevated through polkit), and shows live
 RX/TX counters from /sys/class/net.
 .
 The application follows the GNOME Human Interface Guidelines and
 ships a polkit policy so the password prompt is required once per
 admin session, not on every action.
